node.text:
This #WorldChimpanzeeDay, we want to honor our beloved colleague, Joseph Thomas, who passed away in January of 2021 💔

Joseph was a friend, mentor, and respected leader who cared for our rescued chimpanzees at HSI’s Second Chance Chimpanzee Refuge Liberia for over 40 years.

His incredible legacy will continue to live on. Thank you, Joseph Thomas, from the bottom of our hearts, for your strength, determination, and devotion to these chimpanzees. You will always remain an inspiration to us 🙏

node.title: A Lifelong Bond: Memorial to Joseph Thomas

node.text:
South Korean musician, Annie Ko @lovexstereo, was a translator for HSI during the shutdown of a dog meat farm. Little did she know that she would end up adopting one of the rescue pups named DeeJay! 🐾

We are working tirelessly to fight the dog meat trade across Asia but change only manifests when it comes from within the hearts and minds of locals like Annie. The majority of South Koreans are against the dog meat industry and with their support and activism, the end to this trade is in sight.

Together, we can and are making a difference for animals in Asia! ❤

Sadly, thousands of other dogs just like Patou don’t stand a chance without your support. Please, DONATE to help us end the horrific dog meat trade and help all animals who need us the most 👉 go to https://hsi.global/ig010821 or click the “donate” button in our bio!

node.text:
Chewbacca spent his entire life suffering in a muddy pen on a South Korean dog meat farm before being rescued by HSI. Little did this sweet boy know that he would end up being adopted by HSI President, Jeffrey Flocken! 💚

Fast forward to today, and Chewbacca has healed from the pain of his past. His days are filled with constant love, long walks, sleepy naps, and car rides for tasty treats!

Chewbacca means the world to Jeff and his family, and we couldn’t have saved him without your support! THANK YOU for giving dogs, like Chewbacca, a reason to wag their tails! 🐾

node.title: HSI President Adopts South Korean Rescue Dog!

UPDATE: HSI and our partner group, LIFE, are preparing to rescue the 60+ dogs suffering on a South Korean meat farm NEXT WEEK! These rescues are a huge undertaking and require all the support we can get. 🙏

Please, DONATE to save these dogs, shut the farm down permanently, and help all animals who need us the very most. 💔

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Humane Society International in South Korea. May be an image of 1 person and dog.

node.text:
Ever wonder if your support is making an impact? South Korea's Boknal period, in which the most dog meat is consumed, has reached the end of its season. It was reported that many dog meat restaurants were nearly empty compared to previous years reflecting a decreased interest in dog meat.

Our poll showed that 84% of Koreans no longer eat dog meat and 60% of Koreans are in support of a dog meat ban—the highest percentage we've ever recorded!

With your support, we’ll continue shutting down dog meat farms, lobbying for better laws, and raising awareness of the dog meat industry. We've made significant progress in our campaign to end this cruelty and we couldn't have done it without each and every one of you—THANK YOU! 💚👏

node.text:
BREAKING: For the first time in history, Indonesian dog meat traders will be prosecuted after illegally transporting 78 dogs (pictured) bound for slaughter.

Police were able to intercept the trader’s truck in May after they illegally crossed provincial borders with no record of the dogs’ disease or vaccination status.

As members of the Dog Meat Free Indonesia campaign, we commend the Kulon Progo District Police for taking direct action in what now is a major turning point in the demise of Indonesia’s brutal dog meat trade. Click on the link in our bio to learn more.

node.text:
UPDATE: Last week, we identified a South Korean dog meat farm with 60+ dogs awaiting a terrible fate.

Neighbors of the farm reported unbearable sounds of dogs being slaughtered in front of each other, and we stepped in immediately when local authorities and our Korean partner, LIFE, requested help closing the operation down.

Working together with LIFE we plan to rescue all of the dogs, but we need your support! PLEASE, donate to bring these dogs to safety and protect all animals who need us the most 🙏 (link in bio).

node.text:
HEARTBREAKING: Another majestic lion, named Mopane, was allegedly killed by an American hunter in Zimbabwe last week—the details of his killing are all too similar to the devastating slaughter of Cecil.

The perverse pleasure derived from killing iconic animals brought this noble lion’s life to a tragic end. Enough is enough 💔. Click on the link in our bio to learn more.

Every year, tens of thousands of elephants are killed by poachers and trophy hunters for their tusks.
